This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant David Earl Carney in court.  Prosecuting attorney Katrina Voge in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Matter here on defendant's competency to represent himself. Defendant examined by the Court and Court finds defendant knowingly and voluntarily waives his right to an attorney. Court ordered matter adjourned for status. Case is adjourned to Br. 1.
Status conference scheduled for December 1, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Defendant David Earl Carney appeared by video.  Prosecuting attorney Olivia Simmons appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a pre-trial conference. Defendant does NOT qualify for public defender representation. Defendant requests to represent himself. Case adjourned to Branch 1.
Status conference scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 09:30 am.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON 9/14/2022. IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR, A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with JW.

Defendant David Carney in court. Attorney Jack Eichorst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 01.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant.  Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant was given a referral to the Public Defender's Office. Defendant MAY be Public Defender eligible.  
The case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Br. 01.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant David Earl Carney not in court.  Michelle A. Grasso appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. The forfeiture order is stayed for 30 days pending notice to the defendant. Court makes a finding that there is no possible victim identified, therefore, restitution is not an issue.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 3/17/22 @ 2:30p
